Juventus Ties at Napoli to Increase Serie A Lead; Barcelona Wins in Spain

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-11-29T22:54:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-29/juventus-ties-at-napoli-to-increase-serie-a-lead-barcelona-wins-in-spain.html
Juventus rallied to draw 3-3 at
Napoli to maintain its unbeaten start in Italian soccer’s Serie
A and take a two-point lead in the standings. Barcelona beat
Rayo Vallecano 4-0 in  Spain ’s La Liga.  Goals from Marcelo Estigarribia and Simone Pepe helped
Juventus recover from 3-1 behind in Naples. Alessandro Matri
also scored for the visitors, with two goals for Goran Pandev
and one from Marek Hamsik for Napoli.  Juventus has 26 points from 12 matches, with AC Milan and
Udinese on 24. Lazio is two points further back.  Barcelona cut Real Madrid’s lead atop La Liga to three
points following its victory against Rayo Vallecano. Defending
champion Barcelona has though played one more game than its
rival.  Alexis Sanchez  scored twice, with David Villa and Lionel
Messi also getting goals at the Camp Nou.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 James Cone  at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  